rComments: She's so nice. Her lectures are interesting and fun. It's so easy to do good in her class. Probably the easiest A ever. Usually summer school sucks but she made it enjoyable. Love her!

One of my favorite classes. She really cares about her students and she is always available to answer questions. She gave so many opportunities to succeed, it is impossible to fail this class. Weekly class discussion based on readings, easy bonus points, two assignments, and choice between MC exam or take home. She is amazing & gives great feedback
Such a sweetheart, very interesting lectures. Gives bonus points for pretty much anything and has clear grading criteria. Take-home final exam, always a perk!

Amazing teacher and awesome course. Would definitely take another class of hers. There are lectures every week but if you like the main subject of the class they're good. The teacher is really open minded and accepting - the participation matters but she gives us many options to get our extra points.

As long as you're not afraid of writing you're good. You're graded on 4 things: an analysis of a visual media of your choice, a creative project OR a summary of a book, participation (only reason to show up) and a take-home final exam. Very easy even if you're not in communication
